time required: 30 minutes
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Halve, peel, and thinly slice half the @Yellow Onion{1} (whole onion for 4 servings). Halve, core, and thinly slice @Long Green Pepper{1}. Peel and mince @Garlic{1%clove}.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until golden brown and crispy, ~{20-25%minutes}.

While potatoes roast, in a #small bowl{}, combine @ketchup{2%tablespoon}, @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}, @beef stock concentrate{1}, @ponzu sauce{6%milliliters}, @cornstarch{1%tablespoon}, and 1⁄3 cup water (½ cup for 4 servings).

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add green pepper and cook until slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add sliced onion and cook until veggies are browned and tender, ~{4-6%minutes} more. Season with salt and pepper.

Transfer to a #medium bowl{}; cover to keep warm.

Heat another drizzle of olive oil in pan used for veggies over medium-high heat. Add @ground beef{10%ounce} and cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> If there's excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.

Stir in garlic and cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add sauce and bring to a boil. Cook until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Evenly top beef filling with @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}; cover pan until cheese melts, ~{1%minute}. Remove pan from heat.

Halve and toast @potato buns{2}.

Fill buns with beef filling and veggies. Divide sloppy joes between plates and serve with potato wedges on the side.